The paper deals with the processing of unstructured data to structured form in urban environments, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The use of GIS data and photogrammetric meshes suggests a focus on robotics (RO) and artificial intelligence (AI) as well. The paper also discusses optimization and parameter tuning, which are relevant to machine learning (LG).
